  "original_title": "\u0b85\u0bb0\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0bb8\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0bb0\u0ba4\u0ba9\u0bcd\u0bae\u0bc8 \u0bae\u0bbf\u0b95\u0bb5\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0b85\u0bb5\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bae\u0bc0\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bc1\u0bae\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bc1\u0bb1\u0bc1\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0ba9\u0bbe\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bae\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bbf\u0baf \u0bb5\u0b99\u0bcd\u0b95\u0bbf \u0b86\u0bb3\u0bc1\u0ba8\u0bb0\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "The central bank governor reiterated the need for political stability",
      "author": "Rajeeban",
      "body_lines": [
        "Central Bank Governor Nandalal Weerasinghe told the Wall Street Journal that Sri Lanka's economy will shrink by six percent in 2022.",
        "However, he said that the economic decline could be more than six percent as the political instability has affected the negotiations with the International Monetary Fund.",
        "The central bank governor has mentioned that stable political administration is necessary for the country to carry out negotiations with the International Monetary Fund on major structural changes and to obtain financial assistance from other countries and international organizations in order to obtain essential imports such as medicines and fuels.",
        "The non-availability of an expected $500 million extension last month has intensified the fuel crisis.",
        "Similarly, there has been no progress in the expected one million dollar currency transfer with the Reserve Bank of India and China has not relaxed its conditions on its $1.5 billion currency transfer issue, the central bank governor said.",
        "The central bank governor also said that if Sri Lanka had applied to the International Monetary Fund a year earlier and had started debt restructuring activities while having four billion dollars in hand, it would have made it possible for Sri Lanka to import essential goods without hindrance.",
        "He said that this would not have resulted in the state of the country running peacefully and financial pressure being applied to the public but the government decided to wait and see."
      ],
